  "local_port": 39374,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best online shopping aggregators? For deals, comparisons, etc.",
  "response": "Online shopping aggregators are platforms that allow you to compare prices, find deals, and discover products across multiple retailers. Here are some of the best ones for deals, comparisons, and more:\n\n### **Price Comparison Aggregators**\n1. **Google Shopping**  \n   - Searches across multiple retailers for products and compares prices.  \n   - Includes user reviews and filters for price, brand, and more.\n\n2. **Shopzilla**  \n   - Offers price comparisons across a wide range of products and categories.  \n   - Includes user reviews and ratings.\n\n3. **PriceGrabber**  \n   - Compares prices from thousands of retailers.  \n   - Features product reviews, deals, and coupons.\n\n4. **Honey (via Browser Extension)**  \n   - Automatically finds and applies coupon codes at checkout.  \n   - Tracks price history and alerts you when prices drop.\n\n5. **CamelCamelCamel**  \n   - Tracks Amazon price history and alerts you when prices drop.  \n   - Great for finding the best time to buy on Amazon.\n\n### **Deals and Discount Aggregators**\n1. **Slickdeals**  \n   - A community-driven platform where users share deals, coupons, and discounts.  \n   - Covers a wide range of categories and retailers.\n\n2. **DealNews**  \n   - Aggregates deals from across the web, including electronics, fashion, and travel.  \n   - Highlights the best deals of the day.\n\n3. **RetailMeNot**  \n   - Offers coupons, promo codes, and cashback offers for thousands of retailers.  \n   - Includes a browser extension for automatic discounts.\n\n4. **Brad\u2019s Deals**  \n   - Curates the best deals from trusted retailers.  \n   - Covers a wide variety of categories, from tech to home goods.\n\n5. **Groupon**  \n   - Focuses on local deals, discounts, and experiences.  \n   - Also offers discounts on products and services.\n\n### **International Aggregators**\n1. **Idealo (Europe)**  \n   - Popular price comparison site in Europe.  \n   - Compares prices across multiple countries and retailers.\n\n2. **Trovit (Global)**  \n   - Aggregates products, real estate, and jobs from multiple sources.  \n   - Works in multiple countries.\n\n3. **PriceRunner (Europe)**  \n   - Compares prices from European retailers.  \n   - Includes user reviews and product guides.\n\n### **Specialized Aggregators**\n1. **Kayak (Travel)**  \n   - Compares flights, hotels, and rental cars.  \n   - Tracks prices and sends alerts for deals.\n\n2. **Zillow (Real Estate)**  \n   - Aggregates real estate listings for buying, renting, and selling.  \n   - Includes price comparisons and market trends.\n\n3. **Newegg (Electronics)**  \n   - Focuses on electronics and tech products.  \n   - Offers price comparisons and deals.\n\n### **Browser Extensions and Tools**\n1. **Honey**  \n   - Automatically finds and applies coupon codes.  \n   - Tracks price drops and alerts you.\n\n2. **Capital One Shopping (formerly Wikibuy)**  \n   - Finds deals, coupons, and price comparisons.  \n   - Rewards you with points for shopping.\n\n3. **Rakuten (Ebates)**  \n   - Offers cashback and deals at thousands of retailers.  \n   - Combines deals with cashback rewards.\n\nThese platforms can help you save time and money by centralizing your shopping research and finding the best deals. Choose the one that fits your needs based on the type of products or services you're looking for!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
